@MediaService_HostAddress = http://localhost:8012
@AuthToken = your-jwt-token-here

### ---------------------------------------------------
### MEDIA SERVICE API TESTING
### ---------------------------------------------------

### 1. Upload a file
### Roles allowed: Admin, Instructor, Student
### Note: Requires Bearer Token
POST {{MediaService_HostAddress}}/api/media/upload
Authorization: Bearer {{AuthToken}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=WebAppBoundary

--WebAppBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="test_lesson.mp4"
Content-Type: video/mp4

< ./test-video.mp4
--WebAppBoundary--


### 2. Get media by ID
### Roles allowed: Any Authorized User
### Replace {id} with an actual ID from the upload response
@mediaId = your-guid-here
GET {{MediaService_HostAddress}}/api/media/{{mediaId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{AuthToken}}
Accept: application/json


### 3. Delete media
### Roles allowed: 
### - Admin: Can delete any file.
### - Instructor/Student: Can only delete files they uploaded.
DELETE {{MediaService_HostAddress}}/api/media/{{mediaId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{AuthToken}}


### ---------------------------------------------------
### ROLE PERMISSIONS SUMMARY:
### - Admin: full access (Upload, View, Delete All)
### - Instructor: Upload course media, delete own media
### - Student: Upload profile picture, delete own profile picture
### ---------------------------------------------------
